<p>Alexander Popov is a male Olympic swimmer who represented Russia.

	
		 He has won 9 Olympic medals, including
		 4 gold, 5 silver and 0 bronze. This places him 13th all-time among the most decorated Olympic swimmers. The stroke he was most well-known for was freestyle. He competed at his first Olympics in 1992 and his last in 2000.
  

</p>

